    "To simulate such a setting, we rely on the following procedure for generating samples from the NPIV model: Proposition 3.",
    "Let π XZ be a probability distribution on X × Z with marginals π X and π Z.",
    "Let T: L 2 (X, π X) → L 2 (Z, π Z) be the conditional expectation operator associated with π XZ and leth 0 ∈ L 2 (X, π X).",
    "Sample (X, Z) ∼ π XZ, V ∼ N (0, σ 2) and set U = T h 0 (Z) -h 0 (X) + V and Y = h 0 (X) + U.",
    "Then (U, Z, X, Y) is a sample from the NPIV model of Eq."
